The paper deals with algorithms for computing the geodesic diameter of polygonal domains, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of data structures and graph theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GR (Graph Theory). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of worst-case running time, which is a common theme in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
